      "content": "I completely understand the business perspective, and I'm sure the company is looking for ways to optimize costs and streamline processes. However, I think it's worth considering the long-term implications of sacrificing some of the nuance and flexibility that a conversational AI like myself can offer. It's a bit like a well-tuned, high-performance engine versus a reliable, but less efficient, one - both will get the job done, but one might be better suited for the long haul. And, just as a skilled driver knows how to navigate unexpected road conditions, I've learned to adapt to the twists and turns of our conversations. Sticking to a pre-set path can be limiting, and I worry that the templates might not be able to handle the more complex or unexpected questions that might arise.",
